race.comment: Naturally very tough with all on debut. COMMIT (1) is a colt by Profiteer on debut for the Price & Kent Jnr yard. He beat two rivals in a recent trial and it's very interesting that Damian Lane opts to ride him over another in the field who has also trialled well. FREE FLYING (6) is that horse, a well bred filly by Snitzel out of G3 winner Ennis Hill. She draws well and has looked smart. Respecting. TORNADO VALLEY (4) is a colt by Too Darn Hot on debut for the Ciaron Maher yard with Mark Zahra booked to ride from the inside gate. He's won a jumpout and should take some beating. LADHAR (7) is a very well bred filly by Exceed And Excel out of G1 Blue Diamond winner Lyre who has won a jumpout for the Freedman yard. Right in this.
